\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {0.1.1}{\ignorespaces Simultaneous transfer associated with the reaction $A(t,p)B(\equiv A+2)$. The nucleus $A$ is schematically assumed to contain four nucleons, the triton being composed of two neutrons and one proton. The set of coordinates used to describe the entrance and exit channels are shown in the upper part, while in the lower part the simultaneous two--nucleon transfer amplitude is written in detail (cf. \cite  {Potel:13b}). Of notice that the expression of $T^{(1)}$ violates two--nucleon transfer by exactly $T^{(1)}_{NO}$, channel operative also in lowest order of $v$ in the case of independent particle motion.}}{2}}
